  <h2 class="reveal">How I verified it</h2>
  <ul class="reveal">
    <li><strong>Tests:</strong> <strong>28 of 28</strong> passing (the ten calibration goldens, plus the new round-trip and malformed-token tests).</li>
    <li><strong>Round-trip:</strong> both worked presets, high-stakes and trivial, restore their full scorecard from a shared URL alone.</li>
    <li><strong>Responsive:</strong> no overflow at 375px, motion renders correctly, zero console errors.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="reveal">Why I point to this one</h2>
  <p class="reveal">Good enablement is as much about what you talk people out of as what you sell them on. This tool is the honest half of the job in a single page: it will tell a stakeholder "not yet," show the reasoning behind it, and give them the test that would change the answer. And its own build is a small proof that I trust checklists over green tests.</p>
</CaseStudy>
